{"lemma":"حَشْوُ","slug":"حَشْوُ","root":"ح.ش.#","root_slug":"ح-ش-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ش-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8138"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%92%D9%88%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8138","headword_ar":"حَشْوٌ","root":"H$w","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", like the inf. n., (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stuffing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(PS;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is put into a pillow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cushion, &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and [hence]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cotton:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeds used for seasoning food,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rice &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which the belly of a lamb is stuffed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaA$K","text_ar":"مَحَاشٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", deviating from rule. (TA.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soul"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man. (K, TA.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A parenthesis;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a redundant part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, of speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a sentence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which nothing is syntactically dependent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See Har pp. 85 and 86.]) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A digression."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of either hemistich of a verse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is comprised between the first and last foot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT, &c.) ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Small,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young, camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among which are no great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"old, ones;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA$iyapN","text_ar":"حَاشِيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) so called because they enter, or occupy the spaces, among the latter; or because they go against the sides of the latter: (TA:) accord. to ISk, (S,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaA$iyataAni","text_ar":"الحَاشِيَتَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the camel termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu","text_ar":"اِبْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaxaADi","text_ar":"المَخَاضِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu All~abuwni","text_ar":"اِبْنُ اللَّبُونِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H$Y","text_ar":"حشى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) the pl. [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA$iyapN","text_ar":"حَاشِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaA$K","text_ar":"حَوَاشٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) It is said in a trad. respecting the poorrate,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amowaAlihimo","text_ar":"اَمْوَالِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hu*o mino HawaA$iY","text_ar":"حُذْ مِنْ حَوَاشِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., accord. to IAth, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou of the small,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young, of their camels; such as those termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abn AlmxAD","text_ar":"ابن المخاض"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abn Allbwn","text_ar":"ابن اللبون"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [But see another explanation of this saying voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA$iyapN","text_ar":"حَاشِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H$Y","text_ar":"حشى"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$owN","text_ar":"حَشْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA$iyapN","text_ar":"حَاشِيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like"},{"kind":"text","text":"of mankind; (S;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA$iyapN","text_ar":"حَاشِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest, baser"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basest, meaner"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meanest, sort,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rabble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of mankind, or of the people; (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H$Y","text_ar":"حشى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and Har p. 61;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$owN","text_ar":"حَشْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is of frequent occurrence in this sense]; (KL;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hi$owapN","text_ar":"حِشْوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as servants and the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har ubi suprà, in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HA$yp","text_ar":"حاشية"},{"kind":"text","text":". [See also this word in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H$Y","text_ar":"حشى"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a fulaAnN maEa HaA$iyatihi","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ فُلَانٌ مَعَ حَاشِيَتِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came with those who were in his quarter and protection:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this may be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$FA","text_ar":"حَشًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “a region, quarter, or tract;” servants and followers being in the quarter and protection of their master. (Har ubi suprà.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"بَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino Hi$owapi","text_ar":"مِنْ حِشْوَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is of the lower"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sons of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b8-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hu$owapN","text_ar":"حُشْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stuffed garment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K","S"]}]}}